  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Max Def Coastal Blue is the rare asphalt shingle that genuinely reads blue rather than gray-with-a-hint. The granule blend leans cool, with slate and storm-gray accents that keep the surface from looking artificial. On a south-facing Florida elevation in midday sun, the blue tone is unmistakable.",
      "The granule blend uses a base of slate-blue with smaller portions of charcoal and storm-gray to keep the cool tone honest. Up close you can see the layering; from the street it collapses into one quiet blue plane.",
      "Works best on coastal craftsman, Cape Cod, Nantucket-style, and contemporary builds. Less flexible than gray but more memorable."
    ],
